Date	: 02/02/11
Author	: Dubuc Damien
binary	: Libgmalloc


Resume:
------

This library is a tools to display the heap memory in any executable. 
The display help the users and developpers to understand the problem 
of memory during their executions.
This libray is only enable on Linux system.

How to use ?
------------

	To use this library : 
	- Go to the directory : ${CVSROOT}/gprime/external/tools/gmalloc/
	- (Not necessary) update source file
	- $> make distclean all
	- Copy the library libgmalloc.so where you have your binary
   	- $> LD_PRELOAD=./libgmalloc.so ./{your_binary}

Exemple :
		[gprime@cg99-gpu01 gmalloc]$ make distclean all
		rm -f internal_alloc.o gmalloc.o *~
		rm -f libgmalloc.so
		gcc -W -Wall -fPIC -c internal_alloc.c -o internal_alloc.o
		gcc -W -Wall -fPIC -c gmalloc.c -o gmalloc.o
		gcc -W -Wall -fPIC -shared internal_alloc.o gmalloc.o -o libgmalloc.so -ldl -rdynamic
		
		[gprime@cg99-gpu01 gmalloc]$ cp libgmalloc.so ~/prod/
		
		[gprime@cg99-gpu01 gmalloc]$ cd ~/prod/
		
		[gprime@cg99-gpu01 prod]$ LD_PRELOAD=./libgmalloc.so ./gprime-3.214.1-linux -check
		PRIME 3.214.2 27Jan2011 -check
		MEM> Heap peak 110870 bytes
		
		[gprime@cg99-gpu01 prod]$ 

